name: pytest-reportlog
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pytest-reportlog" %}
{% set version = "0.1.2" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b1f71495699e398a40578c0ff3e73ec01b5a192d108e2bea73dbc7b3fa1f2595

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.5
    - setuptools_scm
  run:
    - pytest >=5.2
    - python >=3.5

test:
  imports:
    - pytest_reportlog
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-reportlog
  summary: Replacement for the --resultlog option, focused in simplicity and extensibility
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - marcelotrevisani
